{"key":"processedPost-25088813","value":{"id":25088813,"first":25087995,"last":25092314,"when":1521977288,"utime":"03/25/18 02:28 PM","content":"There must be a way for gasses to exchange during colonization.<br /><br />During fruiting, it's important to have lots of fresh air.&nbsp; Stale, still air will promote mold growth. Moving, fresh air will promote fruiting because it will hasten the evaporation of moisture from the substrate, which is a major pinning trigger along with at least a few hours daily of bright light.&nbsp; Don't forget to mist to replace the moisture which evaporates due to fresh air exchange during fruiting.<br />RR","title":"Re: Need opinion on fruiting state, To fan or to leave lid upside down?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}